The Minister of Health, Osagie Ehanire, says N6.71trn to fully implement the second National Health Plan within the five years. He stated this in Abuja yesterday when he appeared before the House of Representatives Committee on Healthcare Services and Institutions. He said the implementation of the plan was to reduce maternal mortality rate from the current 576 to 400 per 100,000 live birth of children under five. He described the plan as a strategic healthcare system development system aimed at addressing the most basic challenges especially the primary healthcare system and other levels. What second devt plan, basic fund hold for Nigerian health sector Buhari launches 2018-2022 second Health Development Plan UHC: Govt tasked on funding for second national health development plan